To use github as a repository:
Commands indicated by ()
Step 1: (git status) to see current status of repository
Step 2: (git add "file_name") to update or add a file to github
Step 3: (git status) again to see what you're updating/adding
Step 4: (git commit -m "message to yourself") to commit the changes and leave a message to yourself about what/why you're doing
Step 5: (git push origin master) push the changes you've commited to github
